    <description>Tutanota is the world's most secure email service, easy to use and private by design. Sign up for free encrypted email now.

With end-to-end encryption and 2FA, your emails have never been more secure. The built-in encryption guarantees that your mailbox belongs to you: Nobody can decrypt or read your data.

**Please Note**: This is an automatically updated package. If you find it is out of date by more than a day or two, please contact the maintainer(s) and let them know the package is no longer updating correctly.</description>
    <summary>Tutanota is an email client with a strong focus on security and privacy that lets you encrypt emails on all your devices.</summary>
    <releaseNotes># Bugfixes
 - Imported alarm notifications for events with invalid endValue repeat rules are saved in iOS &amp; android local alarm storage, but can never be deleted [#10664](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10664)
 - "you have been invited to take part in this event" message is not aligned with other elements [#10638](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10638)
 - Calendar Widget displays a timed event on 29 March 2026 as occurring at the same time on 28 March 2026 [#10565](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10565)
 - Exporter gives incorrect DATE-TIME property for Recurrence IDs [#10560](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10560)
 - DST wrongly applied during occurence generation on SDK [#10558](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10558)
 - Imported repeating events with alarms throws exception in Android when scheduling AlarmNotifications [#10519](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10519)
 - Calendar notification for all day events [#2846](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/2846)

